Regarding the linker error after the rebase. The problems seems to be that the watch and watch extension targets inherit the linker flags from "ios/Flutter/Generated.xcconfig", which sets OTHER_LDFLAGS=$(inherited) -framework Flutter. Consequently the link fails, because these targets do not contain the flutter framework. Currently it is fixed by setting OTHER_LDFLAGS="" for the watch and watch extension targets, though it would be more convenient if this manual adjustment is not necessary. As this setting seems to be a side effect of fixing #50568 , do you have some insight if this setting could be limited to the Runner target?
