So far I only implemented it for routes that are MaterialPageRoute. I also add support for CupertinoPageRoute, or all PageRoutes.
With MaterialApp it should work without adding anything. In the case of a CupertinoApp, it uses CupertinoPageRoute so now it doesn't work out of the box.

Working demo code
void main() => runApp(MyApp());

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      theme: ThemeData(platform: TargetPlatform.iOS),
      title: 'BottomSheet Modals',
      home: Builder(
        builder: (context) => Scaffold(
          body: Column(
            crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.stretch,
            mainAxisSize: MainAxisSize.min,
            children: <Widget>[
              ListTile(
                title: Text('Cupertino Sheet'),
                onTap: () {
                  showCupertinoModalBottomSheet(
                    expand: true,
                    context: context,
                    builder: (context) => Container(),
                  );
                },
              )
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

Note: In the original package, I could not edit MaterialPageRoute. Devs always needed to replace their routes with MaterialWithModalsPageRoute.
Now for the PR I've created a mixin AllowsRouteWithPreviousTransitionMixin that out of the box allows transitions to routes that contain the mixin RouteWithPreviousTransitionMixin.
Every route that uses that last mixin will need to apply a method that defines the transition of the previous route.
Eg. MaterialPageRoutes fade in/out, but will scale and translate when a modal sheet route appears.
CupertinoPageRoutes animate from left to right, but should scale and translate when a modal sheet route appears.

