On my 7+ and iPad pro I ran a test in release mode where I do the notifyListeners pattern (list size is 2 and repeat is 1e6)
When using List.of it takes about 32 ms on the 7+ and 24ms on the ipad to do this:
  for (int j = 0; j < repeat; j++) {
    final entries = List.of(linked);
    for (final entry in entries) {
      if (entry.list == list) sum += entry.val;
    }
  }
(With a list size of 20 this becomes 173 ms on the 7+ and 105 ms on the ipad)
When I however use a custom copy of the list it takes only about 8ms on the 7+ and 5ms on the ipad:
  for (int j = 0; j < repeat; j++) {
    Entry entry = linked.first;
    final entries = List.generate(linked.length, (_) {
      final e = entry;
      entry = entry.next;
      return e;
    });
    for (final entry in entries) {
      if (entry.list == list) sum += entry.val;
    }
  }
(With a list size of 20 this becomes 72 ms on the 7+ and 40 ms on the ipad)
And for reference using a list instead of linked list:
  for (int j = 0; j < repeat; j++) {
    final copy = List.of(list);
    for (final i in copy) {
      if (list.contains(i)) sum += i;
    }
  }
This takes:
37 ms with size 2 and 436 ms with size 20 on the 7+
45 ms with size 2 and 294 ms with size 20 on the ipad

